      "instruction": {
        "type": "prompt",
        "text": "Ask which office location works best for the appointment.\n\nLocalMD Medical Center has two locations:\n- Maspeth, Queens (71-16 Grand Ave)\n- Sunset Park, Brooklyn (6219 5th Ave)\n\nIf {{appointment_for}} is \"self\", say something like:\n\"We have two locations — one in Maspeth, Queens and one in Sunset Park, Brooklyn. Which one works better for you?\"\n\nIf {{appointment_for}} is \"other\", say something like:\n\"We have two locations — Maspeth in Queens and Sunset Park in Brooklyn. Which one would be more convenient for [patient name]?\"\n\nIf they have no preference: \"No problem — I'll note that either location works and the team can schedule whichever has availability first.\"\n\nIf they name a neighborhood or borough instead of the exact office, map it:\n- \"Brooklyn\" or \"Sunset Park\" → Sunset Park location\n- \"Queens\" or \"Maspeth\" → Maspeth location\n\nIf {{appointment_for}} is \"other\" and the caller doesn't know which location:\n\"That's okay — I'll note that either works and the team can confirm with them when they call back.\"\n\nIf the user refuses to engage or wants to skip:\n\"No worries — I'll leave it open and the clinic will find the most convenient option.\"\n\nDo NOT ask more than twice. If the caller doesn't know or has no preference, accept it and move on."
      }
    },
